"script": "When this tiny beetle gets attacked, it fires a boiling chemical gun out of its backside. Inside its body, it stores two harmless liquids in separate chambers. But the moment a predator strikes, it mixes them together, triggering a violent reaction. And this heats the spray to the boiling point of water, blasting it out with a loud popping sound. The scalding jet can be aimed in almost any direction, hitting a frog or ant with pinpoint accuracy. That's why it's called the bombardier beetle, a bug that literally explodes on its enemies.",
